{"id": "test-01700", "text": "In sentencing Darrel Voeks, 38, to a 10-year prison term on Thursday, Outagmie County Circuit Court Judge Dennis Luebke said he was \"a thief by habit. \"", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 14, "end": 26, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Darrel Voeks"}, {"start": 70, "end": 85, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Outagmie County"}, {"start": 106, "end": 119, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Dennis Luebke"}]}
{"id": "test-01701", "text": "\"You are self-indulgent.", "gold_mentions": []}
{"id": "test-01702", "text": "You are narcissitic, \"Luebke said at the sentencing, adding Voeks should pay restitution of more than $100,000 to the farming family who had hired him.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 60, "end": 65, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Voeks"}]}
{"id": "test-01703", "text": "Voeks, who was already on probation for prior pig thefts, pleaded that he was trying to pay bills for his ex-wife and children.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 5, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Voeks"}]}
{"id": "test-01704", "text": "But the court heard that receipts showed much of the money went to dancers at strip clubs where he was known as a big tipper.", "gold_mentions": []}
{"id": "test-01705", "text": "One stripper said Voeks offered to give her $3,000 for breast implant surgery.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 18, "end": 23, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Voeks"}]}
