{"id": "test-01791", "text": "Clinton to have more news conferences in 2nd term.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 7, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Clinton"}]}
{"id": "test-01792", "text": "WASHINGTON 1996-12-06", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 10, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "WASHINGTON"}]}
{"id": "test-01793", "text": "President Clinton aims to hold more news conferences in his second term and will have one Dec. 13, the White House said Friday.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 10, "end": 17, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Clinton"}, {"start": 103, "end": 114, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "White House"}]}
{"id": "test-01794", "text": "The president had only two formal, full-blown news conferences last year, one in January and one after he won re-election in November, although he had various other limited sessions with the press.", "gold_mentions": []}
{"id": "test-01795", "text": "White House spokesman Mike McCurry said Clinton \"plans to have regular news conferences \"during his second term.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 11, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "White House"}, {"start": 22, "end": 34, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Mike McCurry"}, {"start": 40, "end": 47, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Clinton"}]}
{"id": "test-01796", "text": "But when asked how frequent these would be, he was evasive, saying, \"periodic, occasional. \"", "gold_mentions": []}
{"id": "test-01797", "text": "\"He enjoys the give and take \"with reporters, the spokesman added.", "gold_mentions": []}
